## 3. Safeguards to Mitigate Wireless Communication Risks

Effective protection against wireless communication risks requires a combination of technical controls, user practices, and organizational policies.

### 3.1 Network Configuration and Access Controls

- **Disable SSID Broadcasting:** Prevents casual detection of the network by hiding its name. While not foolproof, it raises the barrier for attackers ([nibusinessinfo.co.uk](https://www.nibusinessinfo.co.uk/content/what-wardriving-and-how-can-you-prevent-it)).
- **Change Default SSID and Passwords:** Default settings are widely known and exploited; custom credentials enhance security ([Lisbdnet.com, 2021](https://lisbdnet.com/what-risks-and-safeguards-are-associated-with-wireless-communication/)).
- **MAC Address Filtering:** Restricts network access to known devices, though attackers can spoof MAC addresses ([nibusinessinfo.co.uk](https://www.nibusinessinfo.co.uk/content/security-issues-wireless-networks)).

### 3.2 Encryption and Authentication Protocols

- **Use WPA3 or WPA2 Encryption:** WPA3 is the latest standard offering stronger encryption and protection against brute-force attacks. WPA2 remains widely used but must be properly configured with strong passwords ([Lisbdnet.com, 2021](https://lisbdnet.com/what-risks-and-safeguards-are-associated-with-wireless-communication/); [nibusinessinfo.co.uk](https://www.nibusinessinfo.co.uk/content/security-issues-wireless-networks)).
- **Avoid WEP:** WEP is obsolete and easily cracked; networks relying on it are highly vulnerable ([nibusinessinfo.co.uk](https://www.nibusinessinfo.co.uk/content/security-issues-wireless-networks)).

### 3.3 Use of Virtual Private Networks (VPNs)

VPNs create encrypted tunnels for data transmission, protecting information from interception on public or untrusted networks. Using a VPN is especially critical when accessing public Wi-Fi ([Lisbdnet.com, 2021](https://lisbdnet.com/what-risks-and-safeguards-are-associated-with-wireless-communication/)).

### 3.4 Secure Web Protocols and Software Updates

- **Use HTTPS:** Ensures encrypted communication between browsers and websites, reducing risk of data interception ([Lisbdnet.com, 2021](https://lisbdnet.com/what-risks-and-safeguards-are-associated-with-wireless-communication/)).
- **Keep Firmware and Software Updated:** Regular updates patch vulnerabilities in routers, access points, and devices ([Lisbdnet.com, 2021](https://lisbdnet.com/what-risks-and-safeguards-are-associated-with-wireless-communication/)).

### 3.5 Disable File Sharing and Network Discovery

Turning off file sharing and network discovery on devices prevents unauthorized access to shared files and resources, reducing risk of data leakage ([Lisbdnet.com, 2021](https://lisbdnet.com/what-risks-and-safeguards-are-associated-with-wireless-communication/)).

### 3.6 Use of Firewalls and Antivirus Software

Maintaining active firewalls and up-to-date antivirus software helps detect and block malicious traffic and software that may exploit wireless vulnerabilities ([Lisbdnet.com, 2021](https://lisbdnet.com/what-risks-and-safeguards-are-associated-with-wireless-communication/)).

### 3.7 User Awareness and Behavioral Safeguards

- **Verify Network Authenticity:** Avoid connecting to unknown or suspicious networks.
- **Limit Sensitive Activities on Public Wi-Fi:** Avoid online banking or accessing confidential information on unsecured networks.
- **Avoid Automatic Connections:** Disable automatic connection to open networks to prevent inadvertent exposure ([Lisbdnet.com, 2021](https://lisbdnet.com/what-risks-and-safeguards-are-associated-with-wireless-communication/)).

