## 4. Comparative Overview of Wireless Security Protocols

| Security Protocol | Description                                    | Strengths                        | Weaknesses                          |
|-------------------|------------------------------------------------|---------------------------------|-----------------------------------|
| **WEP**           | Wired Equivalent Privacy, early standard       | Simple to configure              | Easily cracked, obsolete           |
| **WPA**           | Wi-Fi Protected Access, improved over WEP      | Better encryption than WEP       | Vulnerable to some attacks         |
| **WPA2**          | Strong encryption with AES                      | Widely supported, secure         | Vulnerable if weak passwords used  |
| **WPA3**          | Latest standard with enhanced protections      | Strongest security, protects against brute-force | Limited device support currently |

Upgrading to WPA3 or at least WPA2 with strong passwords is critical for network security ([Lisbdnet.com, 2021](https://lisbdnet.com/what-risks-and-safeguards-are-associated-with-wireless-communication/); [nibusinessinfo.co.uk](https://www.nibusinessinfo.co.uk/content/security-issues-wireless-networks)).

